    "recap_headline": "Murray State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "EVANSVILLE, Ind.\n\u2013 Five innings of shutout relief and a two-RBI triple from\nKainen Jorge\npowered the Racers to a 3-1 series-clinching victory over MVC foe Valparaiso on Saturday.\nAfter Valparaiso (6-12, 0-2 MVC) plated a run in the second inning, the Racers' arms held the Beacons scoreless for the final seven frames of the contest.\nJacob Hustedde\nearned the start and tossed four innings, allowing just two hits and one unearned run. Hustedde has surrendered only two earned runs over his last 20.2 innings pitched.\nCarter Boyd\ntook over on the bump and dominated with 3.2 innings of shutout relief. He allowed just three hits and struck out two to earn his first win as a Racer.\nBen Rosin\nclosed out the game to earn his second save of the season, punching out three in 1.1 innings of work.\n\"We got seven of the nine leadoff guys out,\" head coach\nDan Skirka\nsaid. \"Just did a good job of making them work really hard to get on base and get rallies. The one run that scored was unearned; we had to match their guy... it's all about the pitching holding them to one run today.\"\nJorge highlighted the Murray State (15-8, 2-0 MVC) offense with two hits. The most significant was a two-run triple in the sixth inning that drove in the game-winning runs. The triple was Jorge's third of the season.\nConner Cunningham\nput the Racers on the board with his first triple of the year in the fourth inning, scoring Jorge, and making today the first time since March 29, 2025 the Racers have recorded multiple triples in a game.\n\"He's such a professional hitter,\" Skirka said of Cunningham. \"Great approaches, really good process at the plate. As a sophomore, he's already seen some things and played some games, so he's not intimidated. For him to get in there and find some consistency and find health, I think, has been the big thing for him.\"\nKristofer Hokenson\njoined Jorge as the only other Racer to record multiple hits, extending his reached-base streak to 16 games.\nConnor Chisolm\nand\nLuke Mistone\neach added singles in today's contest.\nThe Racers will look to complete the sweep over Valparaiso tomorrow at 1 p.m. in Evansville.",
    "watch_url": null
  },
